/target/aarch64.re — Target capabilities for lowering on AArch64/

/LAYER: target descriptor — what the CPU can do natively./
/Used by the compiler's lowering layer to choose between:/
/- native hardware instructions (preferred)/
/- software fallbacks (when hardware lacks the capability)/

/This is NOT ABI (calling convention → aria/abi/aarch64_sysv.re)./
/This is NOT syscall numbers (→ target/linux_generic.re)./
/This is NOT language semantics (→ aspects.re)./

/XLEN: there is exactly one source of truth — K_XLEN in runtime/layout.re,/
/generated by gen_compiler.py from the _XLEN constant. This file does/
/NOT redeclare it. Anything that needs the word width reads K_XLEN./

/Capability Lux: word = 1 if hardware supports, 0 if software fallback./
/Select  — CSEL instruction exists → branchless conditional move/
/HwDiv   — SDIV/UDIV instructions exist natively (always true AArch64)/
/HwMul   — MUL instruction exists natively (always true AArch64)/

/How the lowering layer uses these:/
/yaku.re checks TGTCAP_SELECT before emitting a Select Lux./
/If 1: emit CSEL. If 0: emit conditional branch sequence./
/This is the opt layer (Select is NOT in aspects.re)./

/DEPENDENCY: aspects.re/

/── Lowering capabilities ─────────────────────────────────────/
/1 = hardware instruction available, 0 = software fallback needed/

NEWSET TGTCAP_SELECT 1    /CSEL available — branchless select supported/

NEWSET TGTCAP_HW_DIV 1    /SDIV/UDIV available natively/

NEWSET TGTCAP_HW_MUL 1    /MUL available natively/

NEWSET TGTCAP_HW_SHIFT 1  /barrel shifter for variable shifts/
